{"title_page": "Zhong Chenle", "text_new": "{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Zhong (surname)|Zhong]]}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Zhong Chenle\n| image              = Zhong Chenle at 24th Dream Concert 04.png\n| caption            = Chenle during an interview on the red carpet of the 24th [[Dream Concert (South Korea)|Dream Concert]] on May 12, 2018\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|2001|11|22}}\n| birth_place        = [[Shanghai]], China\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer|actor|songwriter}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Mandopop]]}}\n| instrument       = {{hlist|Vocals}}\n| years_active     = 2009\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[SM Entertainment|SM]]|[[Avex Trax]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[NCT (band)|NCT]]|[[NCT Dream]]|[[SM Town]]}}\n}}\n| module2            = {{Chinese|child=yes\n|t={{lang|zh|{{linktext|\u937e|\u8fb0|\u6a02}}}}\n|s={{lang|zh|{{linktext|\u949f|\u8fb0|\u4e50}}}}\n|p=Zh\u014dng Ch\u00e9nl\u00e8\n|w=\n|poj= Chiong s\u00een-ga\u030dk\n|first=t\n|hangul={{lang|ko|{{linktext|\uc885|\uc9c4|\ub77d}}}}\n|hanja={{lang|ko|{{linktext|\u9418|\u8fb0|\u6a02}}}}\n|rr=  Jong Jin-rak\n|mr= Chong Chin-rak\n}}\n}}\n'''Zhong Chenle''' ({{zh|\u949f\u8fb0\u4e50}}; born 22 November 2001),<ref>{{cite web |title=Artist Profile |url=http://nctdream.smtown.com/ |website=NCTDREAM Official WebSite |publisher=SM Entertainment |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref> known professionally by the mononym '''Chenle''' ({{hangul|\ucc9c\ub7ec}}), is a Chinese singer, songwriter, and actor currently based in [[Seoul]], South Korea. Chenle started his career as a child singer, having performed in various concerts and television shows in China and abroad. At age 9, he was the youngest singer in the world to be invited to sing at [[Musikverein|Golden Hall of Vienna]] with a solo performance.<ref name=\"introduce\"/> By age 14, Chenle had released three solo albums and hosted one solo concert in China. In 2016, Chenle came to South Korea to join South-Korean boy group [[NCT (band)|NCT]], debuting as a part of their youth sub-unit [[NCT Dream]] and has since been active in NCT Dream activities, so far releasing three Korean EPs and conducted one Asia tour together with the group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nct.smtown.com/Intro|title=NCT Official Website|website=NCT|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nctdream.smtown.com/|title=NCTDREAM Official WebSite|website=NCT Dream|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nChenle was born in [[Shanghai|Shanghai, China]] on 22 November 2001. He studied at Beijing Contemporary Music School. In 2006, he entered the small television station Shanghai Ying Siu Sing School and went to dance classes. In 2008, he was admitted to Shanghai Little Flute Art Troupe and studied vocal music with Huang Jing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://channel-korea.com/nct-chenle-profile/|title=Chenle Profile|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n=== 2009\u20132015: Solo activities ===\nIn 2009, Zhong participated in the Hajj children's channel held by Yueyue Elf Vs Season Trial and won the runner-up and Elf Genie Award{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}. \n\nIn 2010, he participated in the National Chinese Young Talent Selection activities, and won the vocal group a gold medal. On 16 June 2011, as a part of the starring actress Xiao Jiabin attending the second Nie Er Music Week opening ceremony ([[Shanghai Grand Theater]]), Zhong led the audience of thousands to sing the [[March of the Volunteers|national anthem]].{{citation needed|date=March 2018}}\n\nIn January 2011, at age 9, Zhong was invited to perform the song ''[[Memory (Cats song)|Memory]]'' from [[Andrew Lloyd Webber]]'s musical, ''[[Cats (musical)|Cats]],'' at the [[Musikverein|Golden Hall of Vienna]] - at the time he was the youngest singer in the world to have ever held a solo performance there.<ref name=\"introduce\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theskykid.com/introducing-chenle-zhong/|title=Introducing Chenle Zhong|website=Netease|access-date=2018-04-20}}</ref> \n\nIn July 2011, his second solo album, ''My Wings'', was released with a total of 12 songs. On 31 July 2011, Zhong participated in the opening ceremony of Shanghai International Children's Art Festival on the Shanghai Grand Stage and also the Closing Ceremony of Shanghai International Children's Art Festival at [[Shanghai International Convention Center]] on 4 August 2011.{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nZhong began his professional career as a singer after competing in singing competitions such as ''[[China's Got Talent]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.qq.com/a/20100930/000128.htm|title=\"\u8fbe\u4eba\"\u9009\u624b\u56fd\u5e86\u5fd9 \u5f20\u5fd7\u6797\u7b7e\u4e0b\u97f3\u4e50\u8fbe\u4eba\u949f\u8fb0\u4e50|website=Tencent|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref> He has released 3 albums.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/10/0930/07/6HQI56PH00032DGD.html|title=8\u5c81\"\u8fbe\u4eba\"\u949f\u8fb0\u4e50\u88ab\u7b7e \u8981\u53d1\u4e13\u8f91\u300a\u5929\u7c41\u7ae5\u58f0\u300b|website=Netease|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref> He used to do [[Cover version|cover songs]] and upload them to [[YouTube]]. Many of his covers are of former child star [[Declan Galbraith]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theskykid.com/introducing-chenle-zhong/|title=Introducing Chenle Zhong|website=Netease|access-date=2018-04-20}}</ref>  He is part of the World Organization of Child Ambassadors of Peace with HQ in Washington, DC, founded and presided by pianist, songwriter and producer, Ezekiel Elkin, representing China as a young cultural diplomat around the world. He was the Chinese Ambassador at The Musical Summit, an international multicultural show created by Elkin which took place in Buenos Aires City in August 2014 where he performed \"The Dragon's Romance\", a song Elkin wrote especially for him. \n\nIn December 2012, Zhong participated in the first Plenary Session of the Huangpu District of Shanghai, and elected the district chief with the highest votes. His first known acting minor roles were in 2013 when he was 11 years old, he was featured in Chinese Drama, ''[[The Queen of SOP|The Queen of SOP 2]]''. In 2014, he held a solo concert at the [[Shanghai Concert Hall]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/y/2014-02-18/17104098686.shtml|title=\u949f\u8fb0\u4e50\u4e0a\u6d77\u97f3\u4e50\u5385\u6f14\u5531\u4f1a\u5706\u6ee1\u843d\u5e55|date=18 February 2014|website=Sina|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Debut with NCT ===\nIn August 2016, he started doing activities in South Korea by debuting as a member of the sub-unit [[NCT Dream]], a rotational unit of [[NCT (band)|NCT]] consisting of teenage members. He is one of the two members in the entire group alongside Renjun (the other Chinese member of NCT Dream) who was not introduced as a part of [[SM Rookies]] before the group's debut. He debuted in NCT after only 2 months of training.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://korea.people.com.cn/n3/2016/0819/c205178-9102771-2.html|title=SM\u65b0\u7537\u56e2NCT DREAM\u5c06\u4e8e25\u65e5\u51fa\u9053 14\u5c81\u4e2d\u56fd\u7c4d\u6210\u5458\u516c\u5f00|website=People's Daily|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|NCT discography}}\n\n===Albums===\n* ''Tomorrow'' (2010)\n* ''My Wings'' (2011)\n* ''You Are There'' (2014)\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Notes\n|-\n| 2011 || Yellow Maple Leave || Shanghai Art Humanities Channel \"Time Song\" Premiere\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\"|2012 || Strong Children || A sound of a guitar accompaniment solo\n|-\n|  Do Not Be Afraid || Movie: \"Monster Wanted Order\" theme song\n|-\n|  Amazing Grace || Shenzhen Satellite TV \"Beware 00\" Opening Remarks\n|-\n|  An Angel || Shenzhen TV \"The Mysterious Baby Mid-Autumn Festival Concert with Rice\" Premiere\n|-\n|  Childhood Companion || \"Jade Qiaolin Story\" OST\n|-\n|  Travel The Wind|| \"Jade Qiaolin Story\" theme song\n|-\n|  Ben || rowspan=\"2\" | Cover Song\n|-\n|  Eyes on Me \n|-\n|  Can You Feel The Love Tonight || Movie: \"[[The Lion King]]\" Theme Song\n|-\n| 2014 || \u9f99\u6708\u60c5\u7f18 (The Dragon's Romance) || Wunderkindz by \"Zeke & The Kiddos\" (The Musical Summit) in Buenos Aires City, Argentina\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n===Films===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Title in Mandarin !! Notes\n|-\n| 2013 ||''Soul Rhythm''|| \u9748\u9b42\u7684\u7bc0\u594f ||Pre-debut\n|-\n| 2014 ||''A Candy for Mother'' (A Short Film) || \u638c\u5fc3\u7684\u7cd6\u679c ||Pre-debut\n|}\n\n===Television Series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Title in Mandarin !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2013 ||''The Queen of SOP 2''|| \u52dd\u5973\u7684\u4ee3\u50f92 ||rowspan=\"2\"|Pre-debut\n|-\n|''Bund Police''|| \u5916\u6ee9\u8b66\u4e8b\n|}\n\n===Variety Shows===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Title in Mandarin !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2010 || ''[[China's Got Talent]]'' ||\u4e2d\u56fd\u8fbe\u4eba\u79c0 ||Pre-debut\n|-\n|''Sunday My Biggest''|| \u5468\u65e5\u6211\u6700\u5927 ||Performing the song \"Tomorrow\" \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2011 ||''Happy Blue Sky''|| \u5feb\u4e50\u84dd\u5929\u4e0b ||Performing the song \"Memory\"\n|-\n|''We Have a Set''|| \u6211\u4eec\u6709\u4e00\u5957 ||Performing the song \"Memory\" and \"You Raise Me Up\"\n|-\n| ''[[Day Day Up]]'' || \u5929\u5929\u5411\u4e0a || rowspan=\"3\" |Performing the song \"Memory\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\"|2012 ||''Red Star''|| \u7ea2\u661f\u95ea\u95ea\n|-\n|''Talented Children's Voice''||\u5929\u624d\u7ae5\u58f0\n|-\n|''Innocence Hit the Earth''|| \u7ae5\u5fc3\u649e\u5730\u7403 ||\n|-\n|''Table Plan''|| \u540c\u684c\u8ba1\u5212 ||Performing the song \"Memory\"\n|-\n|''Sound One Team''|| \u5929\u58f0\u4e00\u961f ||Performing \"Memory\", \"Tell Me Why\" and other songs.\n|-\n|''The Mysterious Baby Mid-Autumn Festival Concert with Rice''|| \u996d\u6ca1\u4e86\u79c0\u4e4b\u9b54\u529b\u5b9d\u5b9d\u4e2d\u79cb\u6f14\u5531\u4f1a || Performing the song \"Tell Me Why\" \n|-\n|''Beware 00''|| \u5c0f\u5fc300\u540e ||Performing the song \"Amazing Grace\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|2013 ||''Flash World''|| \u95ea\u5929\u4e0b || Performing the songs \"My Songs\", \"Tell Me Why\" and \"Can You Feel The Love Tonight\"\n|-\n|''I Love My Motherland''|| \u6211\u7231\u6211\u7684\u7956\u56fd || Performing the song \"You Raise Me Up\"\n|-\n|''Super Voice''|| \u8d85\u7ea7\u7ae5\u58f0 ||Judge\n|-\n|''China New Voice Generation''|| \u4e2d\u56fd\u65b0\u58f0\u4ee3 ||Performing \"Amazing Grace\" and \"Snail\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|2014 ||''Wunderkindz by \"Zeke & The Kiddos\"''|| \u795e\u7ae5\u4eec || Performing the song \"The Dragon's Romance\" (El romance del drag\u00f3n - \u9f99\u6708\u60c5\u7f18)\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award!! Result\n|-\n| 2009 || Yueyue Elf Vs Season Trial \"Elf Genie Award\" || {{Won}}\n|-\n| 2010 || National Outstanding Students Competition || {{Won}}\n|-\n| 2010 ||  National Award For Young Talents in China || {{Won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{NCT (band)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zhong, Chenle}}\n[[Category:2001 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Singers from Shanghai]]\n[[Category:Chinese expatriates in South Korea]]\n[[Category:21st-century Chinese singers]]\n[[Category:Chinese child singers]]\n[[Category:Chinese male child actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Zhong (surname)|Zhong]]}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Zhong Chenle\n| image              = Zhong Chenle at 24th Dream Concert 04.png\n| caption            = Chenle during an interview on the red carpet of the 24th [[Dream Concert (South Korea)|Dream Concert]] on May 12, 2018\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|2001|11|22}}\n| birth_place        = [[Shanghai]], China\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer|actor|songwriter}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Mandopop]]}}\n| instrument       = {{hlist|Vocals}}\n| years_active     = 2009\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[SM Entertainment|SM]]|[[Avex Trax]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[NCT (band)|NCT]]|[[NCT Dream]]|[[SM Town]]}}\n}}\n| module2            = {{Chinese|child=yes\n|t={{lang|zh|{{linktext|\u937e|\u8fb0|\u6a02}}}}\n|s={{lang|zh|{{linktext|\u949f|\u8fb0|\u4e50}}}}\n|p=Zh\u014dng Ch\u00e9nl\u00e8\n|w=\n|poj= Chiong s\u00een-ga\u030dk\n|first=t\n|hangul={{lang|ko|{{linktext|\uc885|\uc9c4|\ub77d}}}}\n|hanja={{lang|ko|{{linktext|\u9418|\u8fb0|\u6a02}}}}\n|rr=  Jong Jin-rak\n|mr= Chong Chin-rak\n}}\n}}\n'''Zhong Chenle''' ({{zh|\u949f\u8fb0\u4e50}}; born 22 November 2001),<ref>{{cite web |title=Artist Profile |url=http://nctdream.smtown.com/ |website=NCTDREAM Official WebSite |publisher=SM Entertainment |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref> known professionally by the mononym '''Chenle''' ({{hangul|\ucc9c\ub7ec}}), is a Chinese singer, songwriter, and actor currently based in [[Seoul]], South Korea. Chenle started his career as a child singer, having performed in various concerts and television shows in China and abroad. At age 9, he was the youngest singer in the world to be invited to sing at [[Musikverein|Golden Hall of Vienna]] with a solo performance.<ref name=\"introduce\"/> By age 14, Chenle had released three solo albums and hosted one solo concert in China. In 2016, Chenle came to South Korea to join South-Korean boy group [[NCT (band)|NCT]], debuting as a part of their youth sub-unit [[NCT Dream]] and has since been active in NCT Dream activities, so far releasing three Korean EPs and conducted one Asia tour together with the group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nct.smtown.com/Intro|title=NCT Official Website|website=NCT|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nctdream.smtown.com/|title=NCTDREAM Official WebSite|website=NCT Dream|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nChenle was born in [[Shanghai|Shanghai, China]] on 22 November 2001. He studied at Beijing Contemporary Music School. In 2006, he entered the small television station Shanghai Ying Siu Sing School and went to dance classes. In 2008, he was admitted to Shanghai Little Flute Art Troupe and studied vocal music with Huang Jing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://channel-korea.com/nct-chenle-profile/|title=Chenle Profile|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n=== 2009\u20132015: Solo activities ===\nIn 2009, Zhong participated in the Hajj children's channel held by Yueyue Elf Vs Season Trial and won the runner-up and Elf Genie Award{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}. \n\nIn 2010, he participated in the National Chinese Young Talent Selection activities, and won the vocal group a gold medal. On 16 June 2011, as a part of the starring actress Xiao Jiabin attending the second Nie Er Music Week opening ceremony ([[Shanghai Grand Theater]]), Zhong led the audience of thousands to sing the [[March of the Volunteers|national anthem]].{{citation needed|date=March 2018}}\n\nIn January 2011, at age 9, Zhong was invited to perform the song ''[[Memory (Cats song)|Memory]]'' from [[Andrew Lloyd Webber]]'s musical, ''[[Cats (musical)|Cats]],'' at the [[Musikverein|Golden Hall of Vienna]] - at the time he was the youngest singer in the world to have ever held a solo performance there.<ref name=\"introduce\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theskykid.com/introducing-chenle-zhong/|title=Introducing Chenle Zhong|website=Netease|access-date=2018-04-20}}</ref> \n\nIn July 2011, his second solo album, ''My Wings'', was released with a total of 12 songs. On 31 July 2011, Zhong participated in the opening ceremony of Shanghai International Children's Art Festival on the Shanghai Grand Stage and also the Closing Ceremony of Shanghai International Children's Art Festival at [[Shanghai International Convention Center]] on 4 August 2011.{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nZhong began his professional career as a singer after competing in singing competitions such as ''[[China's Got Talent]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.qq.com/a/20100930/000128.htm|title=\"\u8fbe\u4eba\"\u9009\u624b\u56fd\u5e86\u5fd9 \u5f20\u5fd7\u6797\u7b7e\u4e0b\u97f3\u4e50\u8fbe\u4eba\u949f\u8fb0\u4e50|website=Tencent|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref> He has released 3 albums.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/10/0930/07/6HQI56PH00032DGD.html|title=8\u5c81\"\u8fbe\u4eba\"\u949f\u8fb0\u4e50\u88ab\u7b7e \u8981\u53d1\u4e13\u8f91\u300a\u5929\u7c41\u7ae5\u58f0\u300b|website=Netease|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref> He used to do [[Cover version|cover songs]] and upload them to [[YouTube]]. Many of his covers are of former child star [[Declan Galbraith]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theskykid.com/introducing-chenle-zhong/|title=Introducing Chenle Zhong|website=Netease|access-date=2018-04-20}}</ref>  He is part of the World Organization of Child Ambassadors of Peace with HQ in Washington, DC, founded and presided by pianist, songwriter and producer, Ezekiel Elkin, representing China as a young cultural diplomat around the world. He was the Chinese Ambassador at The Musical Summit, an international multicultural show created by Elkin which took place in Buenos Aires City in August 2014 where he performed \"The Dragon's Romance\", a song Elkin wrote especially for him. \n\nIn December 2012, Zhong participated in the first Plenary Session of the Huangpu District of Shanghai, and elected the district chief with the highest votes. His first known acting minor roles were in 2013 when he was 11 years old, he was featured in Chinese Drama, ''[[The Queen of SOP|The Queen of SOP 2]]''. In 2014, he held a solo concert at the [[Shanghai Concert Hall]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/y/2014-02-18/17104098686.shtml|title=\u949f\u8fb0\u4e50\u4e0a\u6d77\u97f3\u4e50\u5385\u6f14\u5531\u4f1a\u5706\u6ee1\u843d\u5e55|date=18 February 2014|website=Sina|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Debut with NCT ===\nIn August 2016, he started doing activities in South Korea by debuting as a member of the sub-unit [[NCT Dream]], a rotational unit of [[NCT (band)|NCT]] consisting of teenage members. He is one of the two members in the entire group alongside Renjun (the other Chinese member of NCT Dream) who was not introduced as a part of [[SM Rookies]] before the group's debut. He debuted in NCT after only 2 months of training.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://korea.people.com.cn/n3/2016/0819/c205178-9102771-2.html|title=SM\u65b0\u7537\u56e2NCT DREAM\u5c06\u4e8e25\u65e5\u51fa\u9053 14\u5c81\u4e2d\u56fd\u7c4d\u6210\u5458\u516c\u5f00|website=People's Daily|access-date=2018-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|NCT discography}}\n===Albums===\n* ''Tomorrow'' (2010)\n* ''My Wings'' (2011)\n* ''You Are There'' (2014)\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Notes\n|-\n| 2011 || Yellow Maple Leave || Shanghai Art Humanities Channel \"Time Song\" Premiere\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\"|2012 || Strong Children || A sound of a guitar accompaniment solo\n|-\n|  Do Not Be Afraid || Movie: \"Monster Wanted Order\" theme song\n|-\n|  Amazing Grace || Shenzhen Satellite TV \"Beware 00\" Opening Remarks\n|-\n|  An Angel || Shenzhen TV \"The Mysterious Baby Mid-Autumn Festival Concert with Rice\" Premiere\n|-\n|  Childhood Companion || \"Jade Qiaolin Story\" OST\n|-\n|  Travel The Wind|| \"Jade Qiaolin Story\" theme song\n|-\n|  Ben || rowspan=\"2\" | Cover Song\n|-\n|  Eyes on Me \n|-\n|  Can You Feel The Love Tonight || Movie: \"[[The Lion King]]\" Theme Song\n|-\n| 2014 || \u9f99\u6708\u60c5\u7f18 (The Dragon's Romance) || Wunderkindz by \"Zeke & The Kiddos\" (The Musical Su